Place Great Northern beans into a large container and cover with several inches of cool water; let stand 8 hours to overnight. Drain. Place beans in a pot and cover with salted water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until beans are tender, about 45 minutes. Drain and run beans under cold water to cool. Combine red bell peppers and asparagus in a pot and cover with water; bring to a boil and cook until tender, about 3 minutes. Drain and rinse under cold water. Whisk olive oil, vinegar, parsley, shallot, salt, and pepper together in a bowl until dressing is smooth. Combine beans, red bell pepper, and asparagus in a bowl; pour 2/3 of the dressing over mixture and toss gently. Add more dressing if desired.